[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926946&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926946&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Before people start jumping to conclusions about what part of the system
we should start patching, I'd like to see the results of some
comprehensive experiments.  Are inverse-queries all that's bad, or are
name queries slow too?  Are the roots the cause of one or both problems
or not?  If so are the root servers overloaded or is it network
congestion?  Is anyone working on this?  We've probably built the
largest distributed database in the world by several measures, so it
would be nice to have some hard studies of its performance.

Peter
